<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900628-0140</DOCNO><DOCID>900628-0140.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Summit Technology Inc.</HL><DATE>06/28/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BEAM</CO><IN>MEDICAL AND BIOTECHNOLOGY (MTC)</IN><LP>   WATERTOWN, Mass. -- Summit Technology Inc. said the firstpatients have been treated with its excimer laser to removecoronary artery blockage while undergoing coronary arterybypass grafts, at the University of Rochester, N.Y. Summitsaid the arteries were successfully unblocked.   The technology of removing artery blockage with excimerlasers has been tested using other lasers at severaldifferent U.S. medical centers.</LP><TEXT>   Summit, a maker of medical excimer laser systems, saidclinical trials in angioplasty are another medicalapplication for its lasers. Summit lasers are also used forthe treatment of vision disorders.</TEXT></DOC>